'''Desanne''' was an [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] from [[Kalist VI/Legends|Kalist VI]]. Due to a political blunder in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] Desanne was stripped of most official duties and relegated to shuttling dignitaries and high-ranking Imperial officials. After [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] failed to catch [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] on [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]], Vader had Desanne bring his shuttle to transport him to the [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']].

==Biography==
Desanne, a [[Human/Legends|human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]], hailed from the [[Planet/Legends|Planet]] [[Kalist VI/Legends|Kalist VI]] in the [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]]. During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], he served in the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] as a [[Commander/Legends|Commander]]. He was stripped of most official duties due to a political blunder in the [[Standard year|year]] [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], and as a result, he was relegated to shuttling dignitaries and high-ranking Imperials.<ref name="Customizable Card game" /><ref name="Encyclopedia">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

That year, Desanne was present in [[Hologram/Legends|holographic]] form during a conference of twenty other [[Battleship/Legends|battleships]] aboard the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|Star Dreadnought]] ''[[Executor/Legends|Executor]]'', the flagship of the Sith [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], to discuss the whereabouts of a [[Corellia]]n [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]], the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], which had escaped the secret [[Echo Base/Legends|Rebel base]] during the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]. During the meeting, at least one [[Unidentified Imperial captain (asteroid victim)|officer]] was killed when an [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]] hit the [[Bridge (starship)/Legends|bridge]] of his [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]].<ref name="TESB" />

Later, Desanne was on [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]], with a small unit of Imperial [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] accompanying him. After Vader tracked the freighter to the city, he captured the ship's pilot, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and the rest of its crew. Sometime later, he also encountered [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], the young man who blew up the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]] three years prior. They dueled, and Skywalker eventually escaped Vader's wrath, along with what remained of the ''Falcon''{{'s}} crew. Desanne and his stormtroopers later accompanied Vader,<ref name="Encyclopedia" /> who told Desanne to alert his Star Destroyer to prepare for his arrival. They then entered a [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class shuttle]] and departed towards the ''Executor'' to continue the pursuit.<ref name="TESB" />

==Personality and traits==
Desanne had [[Color/Legends|brown]] hair and light skin.<ref name="TESB" />

==Equipment==
Desanne wore the standard-issue [[Imperial officer's uniform/Legends|Imperial officer's uniform]]. He had one [[Code cylinder/Legends|code cylinder]], and his [[Rank insignia plaque/Legends|rank insignia plaque]] displayed six red and blue squares.<ref name="TESB" />

==Behind the scenes==
Desanne first appeared as an unnamed Imperial officer accompanying Vader in the [[1980]] film [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']].<ref name="TESB" /> In the film, he was portrayed by English actor [[Patrick Ginter]], who was uncredited for his role.<ref name="PG Starnow">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starnow.co.uk/patrickginter|text=Patrick Ginter-Starnow Account|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/kBZtw|archivedate=2021-06-24}}</ref><ref name="Autograph">'' {{WebCite|url=https://planetdagobah.com/autographclassitrilogy.htm|text=Autograph Classic Trilogy|archivedate=20171115021856}}''</ref> Ginter's scenes on Bespin were likely filmed on [[July 6]], [[1979]].<ref name="Making of TESB">''[[The Making of The Empire Strikes Back]]''</ref> According to Ginter, he also appeared as Desanne in holographic form, to [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Lorth Needa/Legends|Lorth Needa's]] right.<ref name="Autograph" /> He was later given a name and a brief backstory in the [[November]] [[1997]] ''[[Cloud City Limited]]'' expansion set of the ''[[Star Wars Customizable Card Game]]''.<ref name="Customizable Card game" />

